%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4/vllm-orchestrator-gateway.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(PII, regex, etc.)
    participant LLM as vLLM Model Server<br/>(Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct)

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 1: Non-Streaming Chat Completion with Detection

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authorization header
    Note over Gateway: Inject detector config into payload<br/>based on route configuration
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>HTTP or HTTPS (optional mTLS)<br/>Forward Authorization + X-Forwarded-* headers
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run configured detectors<br/>(input classification)
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results
    Orchestrator->>LLM: Forward to LLM for inference
    LLM-->>Orchestrator: Generated completion
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run output detectors
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Output detection results
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: JSON response with detections
    Note over Gateway: If detections found & fallback_message<br/>configured, replace content
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (200 OK)

    Note over Client,LLM: Flow 2: Streaming Chat Completion with Detection (SSE)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>stream: true<br/>HTTP plaintext
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>stream: true<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (optional mTLS)
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run input detectors
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Input detection results
    Orchestrator->>LLM: Forward to LLM (streaming)

    loop SSE Chunks
        LLM-->>Orchestrator: SSE chunk
        Orchestrator-->>Gateway: SSE chunk (with detection info)
        Note over Gateway: Inspect chunk for detections<br/>Replace content if fallback configured
        Gateway-->>Client: SSE chunk (text/event-stream)
    end

    Gateway-->>Client: [DONE] (stream end)
